column8: Minor OS compat updates but otherwise nothing major here.
The new uses of unsafe to access getsockopt/setsockopt look reasonable.
Adds support for ESP-IDF and Sony Vita targets. New `unsafe` blocks are for a\nVita-specific `libc` call to `setsockopt` for non-blocking behaviour.\n
Adds support for Sony Vita targets. New `unsafe` blocks are for Vita-specific\n`libc` calls to `getsockopt` and `setsockopt` for non-blocking behaviour.\n
